            <thetext>By now we map the pointer events thrown by IE 10 and IE 11 to touch events.

The problem is, that pointermove does not include a  touch list with all touch currently available on the display. It only provides a &quot;pointerId&quot;. With this you can distinguish between the touches. 

We have to calculate the touch list by ourself and attach it to our normalized touchmove event.</thetext>
